text: It's been a little bit since I've unclogged a printer (read: since Teddy's Make Teddy Obsolete Workshop). What's the process? <@UVA4Q0DM3> <@UUYJ7QWNP> <@UVCATTNCW> Someone else could fix it on their next shift but I would love to learn!

elements.text: It's been a little bit since I've unclogged a printer (read: since Teddy's Make Teddy Obsolete Workshop). What's the process?
Someone else could fix it on their next shift but I would love to learn!

text:
Easiest is to heat the nozzle a bit over the material temp (say, maybe 230 degrees), then manually extrude material until it comes out. Usually heat creep caused some material to melt and solidify in the heat break so this will fix it by causing the same problem again. 

Alternative method might be to remove the filament and reload, or to remove the filament and nozzle (but that’s probably last resort)
